label: Brainy Actz
name: Mystery at the Lost Pointe Lodge
description: Dr. Gunther Guiles was an accomplished and respected historian, known best for his research on the mysterious unknown. He decides to retreat to his cabin far away from civilization to record the extraordinary discovery from his latest research. Quite some time has passed since his retreat and no one has seen or heard from him in months. It's as if he vanished without a trace! Rumor has it that many of the doctor's discoveries revolved around ancient myths and folklore, with some believing his natural curiosity got the better of him. Could he have pressed too far in his quest to solve life's greatest mysteries? It's up to your group of reporters to uncover the truth and report it to the world!

label: Brainy Actz
name: Legacy
description: Have you ever wondered where the adventures and journeys you experience at Brainy Actz come from? These are chapters in the life of one of the world's greatest explorers, your late Great Uncle. This man has fought off pirates on the open sea, ventured through jungles and been part of multiple inside jobs retrieving lost artifacts and stolen cars. He has amassed fame and fortune that few ever know. He is now giving you the chance of a lifetime. Solve the mysteries and magic that lie within this experience, and his inheritance is yours. Can you prove you are worthy to live "The Legacy"?

label: Escape Era
name: Deja Vu
description: It feels like you've been here before, but you can't remember. Can you solve the mysterious case of Deja Vu?
tarareview: One of my favorites puzzle-wise. I didn't really understand the storyline but the room itself was unique in a few ways.
notes: Cost for 2 players is +$5 each on the weekends

label: Escape Era
name: Arcade
description: Millionaire game mogul stashes money in one of his undisclosed arcades. Can you find the money at this Arcade?
tarareview: A cool room and gameplay in general but when played with 4 experienced players, some of us found ourselves with nothing to do ay times. Would still recommend.

label: MindFox Escape
name: Moriarty's Manor
description: Immerse yourself in the enigmatic world created by Sir Arthur Conan Doyle. This multi-room escape game will transport you and your friends to the Victorian era when life was simpler, but much more sinister. Use your skills of observation and deduction to solve complex puzzles and sneak your way through Moriarty’s Manor to save Sherlock Holmes before it’s too late! The game is afoot!
tarareview: A good classic room with a variety of puzzle types. Good for a small groud of experienced players.

label: MindFox Escape
name: Black & White Café
description: A wonderful introduction for first-time players as well as an immersive throwback challenge for experienced enthusiasts! Find hidden clues and solve puzzles in this single-room escape game with some modern twists. What started out as an ordinary day has become what you’ve only read in the pages of a book. You’re at your favorite cafe to pick up your usual order when, inexplicably, color disappeared from the world. It’s your objective to find the items that will activate the diamond prism before time runs out and you’re trapped in a colorless world forever.
tarareview: Super unique style and lots of puzzles. Would absolutely recommend to frequent players.

label: Great Room Escape
name: Grimbly's Charmed Quest
description: Step inside this peculiar cottage to discover a world of magic and wonder, along with the forest goblin Grimbly who has found himself trapped by a dark charm! Prepare to find potions of untold power, an enchanted Tree of Whispers, and many other mythical marvels on your quest to free Grimbly AND yourselves from the dreadful curse!

label: Great Room Escape
name: Lost Tomb of Cleopatra
description: Your team has found the legendary Lost Tomb of Cleopatra but the sarcophagus and all of her splendors have yet to be discovered. Find her forgotten mummy and you will find her ancient riches!

label: Great Room Escape
name: Art Heist
description: Your team of Top Agents have just accepted a $1 Million mission. World famous artist Vincent Cargot has mysteriously vanished and we believe the infamous NYC mob is responsible. You have one hour to infiltrate his studio, follow the clues and puzzles he left behind.

label: Great Room Escape
name: Mad Lab: Resurrection
description: Join the Mad Scientist in a frantic quest to resurrect the Professor's long hidden radioactive machine, which holds the secret for breaking into his vault! There you will find valuable assets.

label: The Entrapment
name: The Disappearance at Fogmore Manor
description: In part one of the Fogmore saga you open your eyes to find yourself in a dark room. Lightning flashes, illuminating the stained glass windows, and the crackling fire casts dancing shadows over the strange and mysterious artifacts scattered around the manor drawing room. A flickering candle and a scribbled note from your missing business partner are all you can see. So begins your experience in Fogmore Manor.  Are there really spirits inhabiting the strange artifacts here?  More importantly, if there are, are they trying to help you escape or trap you forever? You have 60 minutes to follow the trail left by your vanished business partner. Will you find him, or will the same fate befall you when the clock strikes midnight? Technology, story, theme, and puzzles unite in an unforgettable experience.

label: The Entrapment
name: The Bayou: Legend of the Midnight Raven
description: The second part of the Fogmore saga will take you deep in the bayou where a secret lies sunken beneath the murky waters. A secret that has haunted the Fogmore family for over 100 years. The legends of black magic and mystical portals can’t be real, can they? Could Martin Fogmore’s crimes and his beloved Emily’s curse be real? Tread lightly on the creaky dock and approach the weathered shack cautiously, but don’t believe everything you hear. No one, and nothing, is as it seems and the next twist in this story may be your last. The Bayou is a 90 minute adventure unlike anything you’ve experienced before.  Will you uncover the truth behind the Midnight Raven, or get lost in the swamps forever?

label: The Entrapment
name: London Fog: The Mists of Time
description: The third part of the Fogmore saga will take you back to the unexpected beginning of the Fogmores and their connections to mystical antiques. It’s your first day on the job at Bryant and Cyril’s Mystic Antiquities and you’re off to meet Cyril at a warehouse they have inherited from a mysterious relative. But when you find a 100 year old letter from Cyril you suddenly find yourself in another time and place, and a shadowy organization that’s up to no good will do anything to prevent you from escaping the past and saving the future.
tarareview: The room itself was AMAZING, some incredible mechanics and overall really well done in terms of props, decor, etc. Very challenging. One of my top 3 rooms.

label: Lock It Escape
name: High Noon Saloon
description: Welcome  to the old west! Here at the High Noon Saloon the Outlaws run the town. In their latest heist they stole gold from a mine. One of the Outlaws took more then his share. Find the missing gold, break into the High Noon Saloon and find the gold before the Outlaws return at High Noon!

label: Lock It Escape
name: Nightmare After Christmas
description: Mr. Pumpkin followed Jack into the holiday forest and found the holiday trees. He bagged up something from each holiday to make the holidays bow down to their knees. It is up to you to solves the clues to fix what he has done. If you can’t before time is up, I suggest you better run!

label: Red Door Escape Room (San Diego)
name: Captain Maniacal's Lair-Bratorium
description: ON THE EVE OF HIS GREATEST INVENTION, CAPTAIN MANIACAL, IS HELL-BENT ON BRINGING HIS ROBOT, JAVIER II TO LIFE, AND HIS USUAL ASSISTANT HAS PROVEN TO BE UNHELPFUL. PUT YOUR LAB SKILLS TO THE TEST, ASSEMBLE THE ROBOT, AND BECOME MANIACAL’S TRUSTED HENCHMEN!

label: Red Door Escape Room (San Diego)
name: The Gift
description: LOCKED AWAY IN AN ANTIQUE SHOP LIES A SWORD RUMORED TO HAVE VALUE BEYOND MEASURE. A MAN CLAIMING TO BE THE ORIGINAL OWNER HAS HIRED YOU TO STEAL IT FOR HIM. YOUR JOB IS TO BREAK IN, RETRIEVE THE SWORD, AND DISAPPEAR WITHOUT A TRACE. WILL YOU MAKE IT OUT BEFORE YOU GET CAUGHT?

label: Red Door Escape Room (San Diego)
name: Prison Break
description: THE AUTHORITIES ARE CONVINCED THAT YOU POSSESS POWERS THAT MAKE YOU DANGEROUS. YOUR CELLMATES HAVE CREATED A DISTRACTION AND ARE COUNTING ON YOU FOR A CHANCE AT FREEDOM. MOVE QUICKLY AND ESCAPE BEFORE THE GUARDS CATCH YOU!

label: Red Door Escape Room (San Diego)
name: Fair Game
description: A MYSTERIOUS CIRCUS HAS COME TO TOWN AND THINGS ARE NOT WHAT THEY SEEM. STEP RIGHT UP TO THE TOOTH TOSS, ENTER THE FUNHOUSE, OR CATCH A SHOW. USE A COMBINATION OF WIT AND WHIMSY TO DECIPHER THE CLUES HIDDEN WITHIN THE FAIRGROUNDS. DETERMINE WHAT’S REAL OR WHAT’S JUST SMOKE AND MIRRORS.

label: Red Door Escape Room (San Diego)
name: Once Upon a Time
description: THREE MAGICAL ITEMS OF IMMENSE POWER HAVE BEEN STOLEN AND HIDDEN IN A CASTLE. IN THE RIGHT HANDS, THEY CAN BRING PROSPERITY TO THE REALM. BUT IN THE WRONG HANDS, DESTRUCTION AND DESPAIR ARE CERTAIN TO COME. MAKE YOUR WAY THROUGH THE ENCHANTED FOREST, SEARCH THE CASTLE, AND RETRIEVE THE ITEMS BEFORE THE STORY COMES TO AN END!

label: Red Door Escape Room (San Diego)
name: Confinement
description: YOU’RE TRAPPED IN A NIGHTMARE! REALITY BECOMES DISTANT AS YOU SLIP FURTHER INTO THE UNKNOWN. YOUR ONLY CHANCE TO WAKE UP IS BY GROUNDING YOURSELF IN MEMORIES AND SHINING YOUR LIGHT INTO THE DARKNESS! WILL YOU ESCAPE BEFORE YOU DESCEND INTO MADNESS?

label: Escape Games SD
name: Wizards and Spells
description: Enter the Enchanted Grounds of the Select Dozen, a school of wizardry for the elite few. Beat Professor Wolfgang Lupus in a race across the school grounds in your entrance exam to the school. Grab your wand and cast a spell, try to get out before the bell.

label: Escape Games SD
name: Japanese Thriller
description: A Japanese reality game show is now accepting contestants for an escape game contest. This game is set in the abandoned apartment of the infamous Japanese serial killer, Futoshi Matsunaga. Escape the place where victims fell prey to torturous atrocities and are now said to haunt the apartment.

label: Escape Games SD
name: Superheros Adventure
description: You and a group of superheroes have been locked in a room by a villain. You have an hour to escape before a bomb detonates inside the room. Can you solve the clues in time to escape or will you be destroyed?

label: Lara's Labyrinth
name: BeWitched
description: You have stumbled upon an eerie cabin in an enchanted forest while foraging for food. The Village Elders have told stories about Halvar, the village’s bravest Knight warrior, who disappeared last year while seeking out an evil witch who had cursed or killed many of your people. You discover that the evil witch turned Halvar into stone, and if you work quickly, you can create a magic elixir and transform Halvar back before it’s too late!

label: Lara's Labyrinth
name: Cannibal
description: You and your friends planned a trip to another city. On the internet you found a companion with a van.... who was going to the same city to visit his relatives. A friendly driver who turned out to be a rural doctor, did not raise any suspicions from anyone in the group, and you set off for the road. Very soon, you started to get drowsy. One, by one, all of you lost consciousness. After a while, you came to a dark, damp place. Don’t sh*t your pants, I’ll be back very soon. Have fun !

label: Lara's Labyrinth
name: The Heart of Bastet
description: Egypt has reawakened! Your team unearthed an ancient shrine to the Goddess Bastet in the Pyramid of Giza. Inspired by the story “The Heart of Bastet,” told by your grandfather before his mysterious disappearance at the same site, you wonder if it was sabotage or something more sinister. As the best archaeologist of his time, your grandfather’s legacy drives you to seek answers. With only an hour of air, you must find the Heart of Bastet and uncover the truth about his fate while ensuring your survival.

label: Lara's Labyrinth
name: DaVinci's Challenge
description: Florence is bustling with eager young minds, all yearning to study under Leonardo Da Vinci. You've journeyed far to absorb his wisdom and are now steps away from your dream. But as you near the workshop, your heart skips a beat. Leonardo has prepared a challenge—a room crafted by the master himself. Are you ready to face Da Vinci’s brilliant intellect, or will you fade into history? Da Vinci’s Challenge is a Historic Adventure set in the late 15th century, during Leonardo Da Vinci’s peak. With friends, you arrive in Florence, eager to become his newest apprentices. You have 60 minutes to navigate a room testing your logic and creativity. Prove your worth and secure your place beside Leonardo!
tarareview: Very cool room, very well put-together. Nothing super special in terms of puzzles or difficulty, but some good mechanical/technical puzzles.

label: Lara's Labyrinth
name: Sheepshank Redemption
description: You’ll be doing hard time in Cell Block 4 ! Prison legend has it that the former residents of Cell Block 4 found a way to escape. Can you figure out how they did it and follow their trail to freedom? You and your fellow block-mates have 60 minutes of unsupervised time during lights-out to find a way to escape your cells and make a break for blue skies!

label: Global Escape SD
name: Police Room
description: You have been framed for stealing 1 million dollars and are in jail awaiting interrogation. Your Mission: Find evidence leading you to the money and escape jail! Are you up to the challenge?
notes: Rooms are wheelchair-accessible, building is not. Contact business in advance for accomodations.

label: Global Escape SD
name: Wizard School Room
description: *No description*
notes: Rooms are wheelchair-accessible, building is not. Contact business in advance for accomodations.

label: Quicksand Escape Games
name: The Family Cabin
description: You spent nearly every school break in the 90s at your family’s cabin. When you weren't fishing, skiing, or raising your Tamagotchi, you and your cousins were playing Nintendo. After reading that a copy of your family's go-to Nintendo game just sold for nearly a Bitcoin, you realize the family's copy of the game should still be at the cabin. Unfortunately, your cousins realized the same thing too. Now it's a race to claim the cartridge! Will you get there first or will your efforts be as worthless as a Beanie Baby?

label: Quicksand Escape Games
name: Speakeasy Nouveau
description: It's the height of Prohibition and speakeasies are all the rage. You don't recall much about the other night, but you do remember putting up your prized Babe Ruth signed baseball as collateral for your tab. When you attempted to settle up, they said they'll just keep the ball instead. Today, you've vowed to get it back. You don't know where that speakeasy is, but you know entered through a barbershop. Now find your way in, get your baseball back, and get out before the mob guys return and give you a slugging worse than that of the Babe himself.
tarareview: Good for newer players; nice decor and a pretty classic rooms with traditional puzzles.

label: Quicksand Escape Games
name: Chinatown
description: The word around Chinatown is that they're hiding drugs inside fortune cookies and planning a big exchange at the Chinese New Year parade. Sources say it's going down at the aptly named Chinatown restaurant. This unit has a brief window after they close to find some evidence before it's spread all over town. So get in, get some dirt, and get out unseen. When Chinese New Year begins, what will your fortune say?

label: Quicksand Escape Games
name: The Diner
description: After a wild night at a mob bar a few decades ago, you took up with the wrong crowd and now you find yourself about to rob the local diner.  This isn't your first gig and you're hoping it won't be your last.  The boys didn't give much detail, but said the prep work is all set; just be in and out in less than an hour.  If you can pull it off, you'll be in the "Money Honey".  On the other hand, if you mess this one up, you'll be writing your own version of "Jailhouse Rock", ya dig?
tarareview: Decor was a bit cheap and cheesy, and the gameplay was pretty good. Would recommend for first-time players.

label: Escapology (San Diego)
name: Antidote
description: Dr. Walter Brandt is a high-ranking chemical weapons specialist for the US government, part of a secret department that is only recognized by a series of mysterious numbers and letters. He’s been developing powerful viruses capable of eradicating enemy forces with deadly accuracy, but now foreign powers have recruited him to develop a powerful virus capable of killing their enemies in hours. He has gone rogue and has become a threat to the US and potentially the entire human race. Now you and your team of scientists are tasked with investigating him and finding the only known antidote to virus TS-51 before it gets passed into enemy hands.

label: Escapology (San Diego)
name: Scooby-Doo™ and the Spooky Castle Adventure
description: The town of Crystal Cove and surrounding areas are being terrorized by monsters and ghosts, and now the local Baroness Maria Richman has gone missing and it is suspected that the ghost sightings have something to do with it! Tasked with solving the crime, you arrive at the same conclusion as Mystery Incorporated. But when you get to the Spooky Castle, Mystery Inc. gets locked out, at the same time you get locked in! You soon realize that they’re able to help by communicating clues via magic portraits inside the Castle. After discovering a secret dungeon and monster lab in the castle, you come to the conclusion that the person responsible almost certainly works in the castle - but who could it be as there are several suspects?

label: Escapology (San Diego)
name: Budapest Express
description: On a fast train to Budapest with your fellow detectives, you find out a man by the name of Sir Clarence Hayden has suddenly been murdered! You’re able to narrow down 5 suspects who were seen in the dining car around the same time, but it’s up to you to nail down the suspect before the next stop along the railway. Moving through the cabins and gathering evidence, the killer knows you are hot on their trail and has decided you are their next target. With you out of the picture, they would be free to escape when the train stops.

label: Escapology (San Diego)
name: Mansion Murder
description: You are Robert Montgomerie, the only remaining direct heir to the Kildermorie Estate and the Montgomerie family fortune. You’re attending a family gathering hosted by your Grandfather, Hugh ‘Monty’ Montgomerie, the 9th Earl of Kildermorie, to celebrate the dawn of the new Millennium. As the guests raise a toast, a scream fills the air…and your Grandfather is found dead in the library. It looks like MURDER, and as the direct heir, all fingers are now pointed at you! Will hidden clues reveal distant family secrets? With the police on their way, can you gather enough evidence and piece the story together to prove your innocence? And the biggest challenge of all: Is it even remotely possible to solve the mystery before the clock strikes 12?
tarareview: Would not recommend; puzzles were very simple to the point where we were able to solve some without actually using the clues. Some puzzles didn't correlate well and the solutions didn't end up making much sense. Game was very linear, we were only solving one puzzle at a time.

label: Escapology (San Diego)
name: Lost City
description: Archibald Tucker was one of the greatest explorers of the 1930s. His tales of adventure were known the world over and his prized journal documented every adventure. In fact, he uncovered a treasure so rare, no man alive had seen it! But a sudden gust of wind slammed the temple door shut - sealing Tucker and his journal inside and both were never seen again. Now armed with the latest technology, your research points you to the exact whereabouts of the lost journal which holds the secrets to finding the treasure and you’ve brought all the materials essential for your adventure. However, once you’re inside, angered spirits awaken and deem you unworthy of the riches held within…Now, as a test, they grant you 60 minutes to prove your worth.

label: The Escape Game
name: Timeliner: Train Through Time
description: Time travel just became a reality in this digitally-interactive escape room adventure. As part of the Time Crisis Management team, you’re tasked with addressing life-threatening issues, no matter what decade they happen in. You can easily hop between centuries, from the Jurassic to Medieval and everything in between, with just one ticket swipe on Timeliner, the time-traveling train. Now, the fate of reality is in your hands — it’s up to you to restore the past and save the future. And you’ll have to hurry! All it takes is one mistake in the past for the entire future to fall apart…

label: The Escape Game
name: Prison Break
description: Many consider Prison Break our most difficult escape room. Players are split into two different prison cells and must work together to get out of a 1950s style prison. A successful escape will include a sneaky trip to the warden’s office. An unsuccessful escape will land you in prison forever. Yes, those are real prison toilets….what can we say? We are obsessed with creating realistic environments.

label: The Escape Game
name: The Depths
description: Are you brave enough to dive into the depths of the ocean to investigate an abandoned laboratory? Well, you’ll have to be in this escape room! The brilliant researcher, Dr. Humphreys, has gone missing and there have been rumors of mysterious experiments since his disappearance. It’s up to you to navigate your submarine to the lab, decipher Humphreys’ research, and discover what he’s been hiding deep in the ocean. Just be careful…you’re not alone in these waters…

label: The Escape Game
name: Special Ops: Mysterious Market
description: As a special ops agent, covert investigations across the globe are nothing out of the ordinary. But your routine search of a spice market leads to an unexpected discovery…Now you’re left to combat an international crisis that threatens the state of the world as we know it. You’ll need to harness all your tactical skills and training if you’re ever going to put a stop to this global catastrophe. Through all the twists and turns you have to ask yourself…how deep does the conspiracy go?

label: The Escape Game
name: Gold Rush
description: The 1800s California gold rush was a time when just about anyone could get lucky with a fortune. No one knew this better than your recently deceased relative, Clyde Hamilton. Though he’s since passed, the prospector left behind quite a pretty penny in gold. As his surviving next of kin, he’s offered you a chance to claim the gold fortune as an inheritance for yourself…if you can find it! You’ve only got 60 minutes to get into Clyde’s cabin and take the gold stash before news of the fortune reaches other greedy ears in town…

label: Steal and Escape
name: The Lost Expedition
description: Your team works for Strategos Enterprises which specializes in the excavation of unique areas. 200 years ago the remnants of an ancient society were discovered and the first expedition was sent to unearth Dig-site 413. No one returned and its location was lost…Until now. Three days ago expedition two departed and yesterday communication with the team was lost. We need your team to complete the excavation of Dig-site 413 and bring back any artifacts you find.
tarareview: Good for slightly larger groups (5 or 6). More technical/mechanical puzzles than average and the room was made very well.

label: Steal and Escape
name: The Neighbor
description: Your mission was simple: befriend your neighbor. After five years your assignment has changed. He’s made his discovery and the corporation wants it! Break into his house. Steal the discovery. Escape.
tarareview: Medium-tech. Good game - a couple cool things, but nothing mind-blowing for experienced players. Good storyline, props, and interactive puzzles. Best for 3 experienced players.

label: Steal and Escape
name: The Missing Season
description: The world has three seasons: spring, fall and winter. It is time for a change! Strategos Enterprises has a plan. Your mission: Travel through the seasons. Find the guardian and convince them that we need an additional season. We need a time to relax and enjoy life.

label: Night Walker Caverns Escape Room Adventures
name: Last Chance
description: Winning the deed to a gold mine in a poker game earned Luciano Chance the nickname of “Lucky,” but his luck ran out after later getting caught with an Ace up his sleeve. So, Lucky set off to California to claim his gold mine believing it was his Last Chance to strike it rich. Upon arrival in San Diego in 1882, Lucky sent away for a mail-order bride believing it was his Last Chance to marry. Upon arriving in Buckman Springs, they learned that the mine was located on the Lost Stickman Tribe burial grounds. According to the locals, the Lost Stickman Tribe cursed anyone who dared disturb the resting place of their ancestors. Evil spirits had guarded the mine for hundreds of years, and others who tried to extract gold from the mine either died or disappeared. Lucky was also warned that parts of the mine had caved-in and was just worthless Fool’s Gold. Being a gambler at heart, Lucky formulated a backup plan – if the mine turned out to be just Fools Gold as rumored, then he would set up a casino inside the mine and bilk the locals and travelers out of their money. Confident in his foolproof scheme, Lucky and his bride rode off into the sunset – but they were never seen again. Will you be able to solve the mysterious disappearance of Lucky and his mail-order bride? If you think you still want to enter the old mine and are lucky enough to escape the curse, we suggest you pause for a moment before you venture into the mine shaft, and say goodbye to your teammates – after all, it might be your Last Chance to see them alive!

label: Night Walker Caverns Escape Room Adventures
name: Gooneze
description: Watch your head and your step as you navigate underground booby-trapped caves searching for the lost treasure of the infamous pirate, Captain William Leg. In 1855, Captain Leg (nicknamed One-Leg Willy after a losing battle with Piranhas) and his crew, MoonaLisa Mermaid and Cigar Sam, sailed a small ship loaded with treasure chests up the San Diego River and disappeared into a large cavern. A few hours later, an earthquake collapsed the entrance trapping the ship. The caverns and Willy’s treasure remained lost until 1953 when a group of SDSU geologists studying earthquake faults discovered a cave system stretching for miles deep underground and culminating in a subterranean lake. They dubbed the caves “Nightwalker Caverns” after learning the caves were used by bootleggers during Prohibition in the 1920s. Newspaper headlines chronicled cave explorers’ encounters with poisonous serpents, tunnel cave-ins, strange electro-magnetic phenomena, and hairy human-like cave dwellers--but no treasure. In fact, the treasure remained just another legend until March 21, 1955, when newspaper banners proclaimed that Chester Klinker, a local developer, had found One-Leg Willy’s treasure map while building an office building. The next day, another earthquake occurred, and Klinker was among several people reported missing. Locals claimed that Klinker built a secret entrance to the underground caverns in the office building basement so he could look for the treasure. Your group has made it as far as the basement door without getting caught by building security. You’ll have just 90 minutes to find One-Leg Willy’s map and search the basement for a hidden entrance to the caverns. Don’t lose yourself or your friends while immersed in this totally goony parody on pirate adventure movies. The treasure has already been lost, found, and lost again. Will you and your group find One-Leg Willy’s lost treasure?

label: Night Walker Caverns Escape Room Adventures
name: Clownatorium - 2 Upside Down
description: Thrills and chills are the theme in this "little bit scary and whole lot funny" adventure game. You believe your friend was kidnapped by the Nightwalker Clowns who live in the Upside Down Caverns located below an abandoned carnival on the edge of town. You'll wind your way through the carnival searching for the hidden entrance to the Upside Down – then your group must find and open the portal which will transport you back to the surface.

label: Night Walker Caverns Escape Room Adventures
name: Hotel Nocturnus
description: The 1890 arrival of Jack Nocturnus to San Diego marked the beginning of a long history of unsolved murders. Jack constructed Hotel Nocturnus over a network of hidden caves where his 2 daughters and his grandson resided for many years. It was later discovered that the hotel had also allowed criminals to stay in the subterranean hotel rooms to avoid capture for a hefty price. After Jack’s mysterious disappearance in 1931, his 2 daughters continued to operate the Hotel. Rundown and shrouded in an unsavory past, the hotel continued to decline until it finally closed in 1992 after plumbers found a body hidden in a wall. Hoping to capitalize on the scandal, the sisters contacted a San Diego newspaper to tell their story and alleging they knew the identity of the infamous Zodiac killer. However, the 2 sisters disappeared before the press conference. The hotel is condemned and scheduled for demolition. Before the dark past of Hotel Nocturnus is lost forever, a local TV station wants to do a farewell piece on reported ghost sightings and evidence relating to the identity of Zodiac. Your group will assist the investigation agency hired by the TV station. Good luck and don’t become another victim of Hotel Nocturnus.

label: Night Walker Caverns Escape Room Adventures
name: Salem 1692 - Spellweaver
description: The year is 1692 in Salem Town, and you’ve been indicted on charges of afflicting with witchcraft or for making an unlawful covenant with the Devil. When the executioner’s keys are left in the courtroom, you escape only to find yourself in the execution yard where unfortunates suffer gruesome deaths before being laid to rest. Your path to freedom requires finding a tortured witch’s hand to open a portal through the Cabinet of Oddities. You can protest and claim innocence all you want in the Court of Oyer and Terminer, but the Magistrate will still pronounce sentence of, “It BeWitchery!”

label: Red Door Escape Room (Encinitas)
name: The Relic
description: AFTER DISCOVERING AN ANCIENT RELIC, A TEAM OF ARCHAEOLOGISTS HAS SUDDENLY GONE MISSING. YOU’VE BEEN HIRED TO CONTINUE THEIR WORK TRANSLATING THE GLYPHS ON THE RELIC TO LEARN ITS PURPOSE. BUT BEWARE, A DARK PRESENCE HAS BEEN AWAKENED. DECIPHER THE CLUES THEY LEFT BEHIND AND SEAL AWAY THE DARKNESS FOR GOOD… OR MEET THE SAME FATE AS THE TEAM BEFORE YOU!

label: Red Door Escape Room (Encinitas)
name: Enchantment
description: DO YOU BELIEVE IN MAGIC? WHILE FUMBLING THROUGH YOUR UNCLE’S ATTIC, YOU STUMBLE UPON A MAGICAL GATEWAY THAT LANDS YOU IN KING OBERON’S GROVE. LEGEND HAS IT THAT HIS FAIRIES HAVE LEFT MANY CHALLENGES THAT, WHEN SOLVED, WILL REWARD THE SEEKER WITH A WISH. FOLLOW THE CLUES, UNCOVER THE PUZZLES IN KING OBERON’S GROVE, AND EARN THE CHANCE TO RECEIVE THE ULTIMATE PRIZE!

label: Red Door Escape Room (Encinitas)
name: Survive
description: WE HAVE BEEN ON THE MOVE SINCE THE FALL OF CIVILIZATION, WITH NOTHING BUT THE CLOTHES ON OUR BACKS AND THE STRENGTH IN OUR HEARTS. THERE IS RUMOR OF A SAFE ZONE ON AN ISLAND, BUT THEY WON’T JUST TAKE ANYBODY. THERE ARE MARAUDERS OUT, HUNTING FOR SURVIVORS, AND WE NEED TO SEND A TRANSMISSION TO BE PICKED UP UNDER THE COVER OF NIGHT. WE NEED TO WORK TOGETHER AND MOVE QUICKLY, BUT BE CAREFUL- IF THE MARAUDERS CATCH US, THEN UTOPIA IS THE LEAST OF OUR CONCERNS.

label: Red Door Escape Room (Encinitas)
name: Lost Treasures
description: THE RUMORS OF THE MYSTERIOUS UNDERWATER CITY OF MYTHOS ARE TRUE! IN THE DEPTHS OF THIS DIGITAL EXPEDITION, YOU MUST UNEARTH THREE SHARDS OF AN ANCIENT MYTHONIAN TABLET THAT WILL REVEAL THE CITY’S LOCATION. BUT BEWARE, THESE SHARDS ARE SAID TO BE GUARDED BY MONSTROUS CREATURES! NAVIGATE YOUR SHIP THROUGH THE DANGERS OF THE DIGITAL UNDERWATER MAZE, DEFEAT THE GUARDIANS, AND UNCOVER THE SECRETS OF MYTHOS!

label: Cinema Escape Rooms (ArtHatch)
name: Nightmare Before You Escape Christmas
description: Zilch has gone missing! It’s up to you and your team to unravel a series of mysteries that transcend Holiday lines... Enter through the enchanted forest door to navigate spooky surprises and magical challenges to find Zilch before time runs out!

label: Cinema Escape Rooms (ArtHatch)
name: The X-Tra Files
description: Welcome to the X-Tra Files Unit, rookie agents. The remote town of Bellefleur, Oregon, is in chaos—residents are vanishing, mysterious lights are zipping around the sky, and the local cows are demanding better security. To make matters worse, Agent Spooky was sent to investigate and hasn’t been heard from since. We’re hoping he’s just buried in a pile of his own conspiracy theories, but there’s always the chance he’s stumbled into something, or SOMEONE far weirder. Your Mission: Start at Agent Spooky's cabin, retrace his investigation, and figure out what’s really going on in Bellefleur. Keep an open mind, trust no one (especially the cows), and remember—the truth is out there... probably. Good luck, agents—you’re going to need it.

label: Cinema Escape Rooms (Main)
name: Villain's Lair
description: An evil super villain with a vendetta against the world has created a poisonous substance that he’s planning on releasing, first to all of San Diego, then the world! We sent our spies in months ago to infiltrate his lab and get more intel, but we haven’t heard from them! With the safety of the entire world at stake, we need your help!

label: Locked Adventures
name: Quest for the Throne
description: You were born into a Royal family and it is your birthright to assume the Throne upon the King's death, but your evil younger brother has exiled you from the Kingdom. You will have 60 minutes to find proof of your birthright, to capture the throne as yours and become ruler of the kingdom.

label: Locked Adventures
name: The Curse of KV62
description: You are in the Valley of Kings and are exploring tomb KV62 when the curse of the Pharaoh's has invoked and sealed off the entrance. You will have to navigate through the tomb and find another way out.

label: Locked Adventures
name: Hunting Dracula
description: Vampires were once eradicated years ago by a famous vampire hunter.  However as the moon rises red, the most evil vampire has returned - Dracula!  Are you brave enough to come face to face with Dracula and destroy him once and for all?

label: Locked Adventures
name: Christmas: Help Wanted
description: Oh No!  The Elves have gone on strike!  Help save Christmas, by finding the missing presents, load up the train on time to get delivered!

label: Escapology (Carlsbad)
name: Batman™: The Dark Knight Challenge
description: Gotham City, a metropolis plagued by crime and injustice, is in dire need of heroes. In response to the escalating threats, Batman has initiated a new Gotham City Guardian training program. You have been carefully selected for the program to attempt a new and intense training exercise that includes stopping a training device Batman planted in the heart of Gotham City filled with a non-harmful chemical compound designed to mimic a legitimate chemical leak without the fatality. The device is fitted with a countdown clock that will release the gas in exactly 60 minutes after your mission start time, so you'll have to work quickly.

label: Escapology (Carlsbad)
name: Scooby-Doo™ and the Spooky Castle Adventure
description: The town of Crystal Cove and surrounding areas are being terrorized by monsters and ghosts, and now the local Baroness Maria Richman has gone missing and it is suspected that the ghost sightings have something to do with it! Tasked with solving the crime, you arrive at the same conclusion as Mystery Incorporated. But when you get to the Spooky Castle, Mystery Inc. gets locked out, at the same time you get locked in! You soon realize that they’re able to help by communicating clues via magic portraits inside the Castle. After discovering a secret dungeon and monster lab in the castle, you come to the conclusion that the person responsible almost certainly works in the castle - but who could it be as there are several suspects?

label: Escapology (Carlsbad)
name: Antidote: Chemical Warfare
description: As a team of scientists working in a secret government testing facility, you have been tasked to investigate the abandoned laboratory of Dr Walter Brandt. Dr Brandt was a highly ranked chemical weapons specialist, until his rogue behaviors and plans to conduct chemical warfare using man-made viruses led him to be a global threat. What was supposed to be a controlled mission has become disastrous and time sensitive after one of the investigators sends vials of the contagious virus crashing to the ground, sending plumes of deadly vapor into the air. You now have one hour to crack the clues in Dr Brandt’s laboratory and locate the only known antidote which is the only chance of saving yourselves, and the rest of the world.

label: Escapology (Carlsbad)
name: Mansion Murder
description: You are Robert Montgomerie, the only remaining direct heir to the Kildermorie Estate and the Montgomerie family fortune. You’re attending a family gathering hosted by your Grandfather, Hugh ‘Monty’ Montgomerie, the 9th Earl of Kildermorie, to celebrate the dawn of the new Millennium. As the guests raise a toast, a scream fills the air…and your Grandfather is found dead in the library. It looks like MURDER, and as the direct heir, all fingers are now pointed at you! Will hidden clues reveal distant family secrets? With the police on their way, can you gather enough evidence and piece the story together to prove your innocence? And the biggest challenge of all: Is it even remotely possible to solve the mystery before the clock strikes 12?
tarareview: (Played at the San Diego location) Would not recommend; puzzles were very simple to the point where we were able to solve some without actually using the clues. Some puzzles didn't correlate well and the solutions didn't end up making much sense. Game was very linear, we were only solving one puzzle at a time.

label: Escapology (Carlsbad)
name: 7 Deadly Sins
description: The deranged minister of Crickley Church decided to kill his entire congregation after their confessions convinced his twisted mind that they had, among themselves, committed the 7 Deadly Sins. After inciting a curse on the children playing in the rooms beneath the church he buries himself alive in the church’s hidden crypt, while promising to haunt the church forevermore. Now it’s up to you to locate the hidden crypt, find the dagger, and drive it through the heart of the evil minister before time runs out. Then, and only then, you will be saved and destroy the curse forever.

label: Escapology (Carlsbad)
name: Lost City
description: Archibald Tucker was one of the greatest explorers of the 1930s. His tales of adventure were known the world over and his prized journal documented every adventure. In fact, he uncovered a treasure so rare, no man alive had seen it! But a sudden gust of wind slammed the temple door shut - sealing Tucker and his journal inside and both were never seen again. Now armed with the latest technology, your research points you to the exact whereabouts of the lost journal which holds the secrets to finding the treasure and you’ve brought all the materials essential for your adventure. However, once you’re inside, angered spirits awaken and deem you unworthy of the riches held within…Now, as a test, they grant you 60 minutes to prove your worth.

label: Escapology (Carlsbad)
name: A Pirate's Curse
description: Captain Goldbeard has spent years voyaging the seas in hopes of acquiring treasures beyond his wildest dreams. But one night, many moons ago, the Captain and his crew landed themselves in troubled water embarking on a quest where few others dare go, aboard an abandoned ship laden with treasure, known as ‘The Soul Catcher’. You only have one hour to break the curse before the sun sets beyond the horizon or you will be left prisoner aboard The Soul Catcher for eternity—and with no escape! Do you have what it takes to find the hidden treasure and beat the deadly sunset curse or will you become the next prisoner of The Soul Catcher?

label: Escapology (Carlsbad)
name: Agatha Christie's Murder on the Orient Express
description: You are world-renowned Detective Hercule Poirot, aboard the famous Orient Express and have just solved the murder of Mr Ratchet, a man found stabbed to death in his cabin after being proved guilty of abducting and killing a young child - Daisy Armstrong - the daughter of a WW1 hero. However, just as you are preparing to deliver your verdict, you find out about a more deadly plan. From earlier investigations, you’re able to narrow down six suspects, but now, you must find the killer and repair the brake lines to stop the train before it speeds off the railway. Failure means certain death for all, while success means solving the most famous crime in history, and saving everyone aboard. Will you gather the evidence and catch the murderer before it’s too late?

label: Top Tier Escape Rooms
name: Atlantis: Dive to the Forgotten City
description: Tsunamis are ravaging the globe. The last diving team discovered ruins of an ancient civilization, but reported nothing of significance. You have an hour of oxygen. Can you discover a power strong enough to quiet the sea’s rage?

label: Top Tier Escape Rooms
name: Outside In: Journey to the Mind
description: Futuristic technology has allowed you to share a subconscious dream state with others. Your renowned team of psychologists must help someone overcome their deepest childhood fear.

label: Top Tier Escape Rooms
name: Pirates of the Mediterranean: The Curse of the Crystal Cavern
description: The remains of Captain Redbeard’s ship, thought to be lost at sea almost 500 years ago, has just been discovered in a remote cave on the Mediterranean sea. No explorers have returned alive, and the events of the crash are shrouded in mystery. Can you survive the Curse of the Crystal Cavern?

label: Top Tier Escape Rooms
name: Operation Avalanche
description: A hunter’s cabin deep in the Montana wilderness has been taken over by terrorists in an attempt to take out the city that lies at the base of the mountain. Do you and your team have what it takes to break into the cabin and diffuse a series of jerry-rigged bombs before time runs out?
